	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Mar 31st 1:17 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Questions to Upper Level Paladins,<br><br>Seriously folks, is there really a problem for us Paladins to join a Raid Party?&nbsp;&nbsp;I just read a thread on a guild forum that most hybrid tanks need not apply or dont bother showing up.  Only true tanks are welcome(Warrior).  Do some of you high level holy knights who are even in a guild have any problems getting in on a Zone Raid?<br><br>I'm a level 34 paladin and one of the things I look forward to is being with an elite group that can be strong enuff to beat a Dragon or some ultimate quests that only a chosen few can accomplished.   This is what RPG is all about.  For me,  my ultimate quest in EQ would be to slay a dragon, whether with a guild or just a part of a group.  I've been hearing that in upper levels rangers and paladins and SK's as well are pretty much worthless.  I dont understand this part and I dont understand the prejudism towards hybrid tanks.  Is it because we truly are worthless when it comes to raiding?  <br>Please educate me why we would be so inferior to warriors at higher levels that it would actually get to point where nobody wants us in a group.  I might as well become a cleric, from what I've read they are the most needed class during group raids.  I've also heard from a level 32 friend of mine that she gets invited to join a guild almost at a regular basis.  I've yet been asked to join a guild.  Maybe its cuz I play with the same people all the time but so is my cleric friend but she gets invites by guilds not because of her grouping skills but just because of the fact that she is a cleric.  <br><br>If this is the case and if there is some sort of prejudism towards hybrid classes because we trully are inferior towards pure classes then what the hell is this class balancing bullsheet for?  I hope that hybrid classes have some sort of value in upper levels, otherwise why should I even bother leveling.<br><br>Advice me, warn me, help me, and educate me on this.  It seems as though an ideal group consist of nothing but Cleric, Warrior, Necro(powerfull DD), Warrior,Cleric, and Enchanters(for clarity).<br><br>Let me know what you all think,<br><br>Thank you<br>Level 34 Paladin<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
