	   <tr><td colspan=2>In my personal opinion, I think it more depends on the person behind the charater rather than the character itself that cuases the predjudice toward him or her.&nbsp;&nbsp; I realize that paladins are not a "perfect" class, but all classes have there strengths and weaknesses. It's finding out how to maximize the classes strengths that really counts.  I have both a paladin and a warrior of close to the same level now and I find that on average both get into pick-up groups at about the same length of time.<br><br> In my experience of raids in the planes and dragons, from what I've heard (personally I haven't been on one yet), it takes more than 1 group fighting all at once to do a raid. In other words, the more the merrier.<br><br>Guild-wise, I chose an "uber" guild that had a strong family style atmosphere that had a falling out of the "power-gamers" looking for the fat lewt leaving the guild. In my experience though it has strengthened the members that have remained and made the game more enjoyable for myself.  I also have a huge cirlce of friends that I can count on the help me with finishing quests (such as soulfire) and they generally bring along alot of their friends as well.<br><br>Sorry, I rambled a bit there :)<br>&nbsp;<br>Dadin <br>54th Cavalier<br>Honored Circle on Xev<br><br>Dwarven Thane<br>Hellwinds - Palomides </td></tr>
